# Plotting

This chapter is utterly incomplete and probably not worth reading.



## Plot a 1D mesh

### On a straight line

::: {#d93ddb7b .cell execution_count=2}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
m = makemeshoninterval(0, 4, 20)
mplot(m) |> mconf()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=3}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-3-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


Nodes hidden if too many.

::: {#ec3d4b1b .cell execution_count=3}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
m = makemeshoninterval(0, 4, 60)
mplot(m) |> mconf()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=4}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-4-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


One value per node

::: {#edc3934a .cell execution_count=4}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
mplot(m, -1.1 .+ 2.6 * rand(nnodes(m))) |> mconf()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=5}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-5-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


One value per element

::: {#0a117dec .cell execution_count=5}
