### Vertical

::: {#a2a7a481 .cell execution_count=7}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
m = makemeshoninterval(π, 3π, 20, t -> [0; t])
mplot(m, -1.1 .+ 3.2 * rand(nedges(m))) |> mconf()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=8}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-8-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


### On a spiral

::: {#219c0fa5 .cell execution_count=8}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
m = makemeshoninterval(π, 3π, 20, t -> t * [cos(t); sin(t)])
mplot(m, -1.1 .+ 3.2 * rand(2, nedges(m))) |> mconf()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=9}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-9-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


### Customize plot

Plot customization works like this:

::: {#26c2cbf2 .cell execution_count=9}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
f, ax = mplot(m, -1.1 .+ 3.2 * rand(2, nedges(m))) |> mconf()
ax.title = "Spiral with reversed vertical axis"
ax.yreversed = true
f
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=10}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-10-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


Documentation on plot axis can be found on the [Makie documentation](https://docs.makie.org/stable/reference/blocks/axis) which unfortunately is quite hard to read.

## Plot a 2D mesh

### Quad mesh

::: {#73f08707 .cell execution_count=10}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
a = 80
m = makemeshonrectangle(9.0, 4.5, 2a, a)
println("Number of nodes is Nn = ", (a + 1) * (2a + 1))
print("Links...")
@time l12 = links(m.topology, 1, 2);
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Number of nodes is Nn = 13041
Links...  0.091282 seconds (1.11 M allocations: 86.504 MiB, 32.34% gc time, 14.82% compilation time)
```
:::
:::


Default color

::: {#c89b5a1b .cell execution_count=11}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
mplot(m, edgesvisible=true, edgecolor=:hotpink) |> mconf()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=12}
![](plot_files/figure-html/cell-12-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


Colors for nodes

::: {#aa286fcb .cell execution_count=12}
